                "actions": {
                    "value": "2"
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The scalathrax disgorges a gout of toxic oil from its mouth in a 15-foot cone. Creatures in the area must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"conjuration,primal,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Spray Toxic Oil DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Reflex</span> save.</p>\n<div data-visibility=\"gm\">\n<p>The scalathrax can't use Toxic Oil Spray again for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes [[/r 1d8 #poison]]{1d8 poison damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes [[/r 2d8 #poison]]{2d8 poison damage}. For 1 minute, the creature gains weakness to fire 5, and whenever the creature critically fails with an attack roll with a wielded weapon, it drops the weapon.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but [[/r 4d8 #poison]]{4d8 poison damage}.</p>\n</div>"
                },
